From 7e0ca7230b980b451c8265fbe75e5bd47fd832a9 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Mordechay Goodstein <mordechay.goodstein@intel.com>
Date: Fri, 11 Sep 2020 20:44:33 +0300
Subject: [PATCH] iwlwifi: sta: defer ADDBA transmit in case reclaimed SN != next SN
Git-commit: 7e0ca7230b980b451c8265fbe75e5bd47fd832a9
Patch-mainline: v5.10-rc1
References: bsc#1187495

This avoids cases that we have a lot of packets in the queue and until we
are able to transmit SSN packet the other side sends DELBA due to timeout.

Signed-off-by: Mordechay Goodstein <mordechay.goodstein@intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Luca Coelho <luciano.coelho@intel.com>
Link: https://lore.kernel.org/r/iwlwifi.20200911204056.8a8481c60663.I353ab6f1bc04c7fdf873dead59f483454e2425ba@changeid
Acked-by: Takashi Iwai <tiwai@suse.de>

---
 drivers/net/wireless/intel/iwlwifi/mvm/sta.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/net/wireless/intel/iwlwifi/mvm/sta.c b/drivers/net/wireless/intel/iwlwifi/mvm/sta.c
index 9e124755a3ce..fc45ef4f6951 100644
--- a/drivers/net/wireless/intel/iwlwifi/mvm/sta.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/intel/iwlwifi/mvm/sta.c
@@ -2863,7 +2863,7 @@ int iwl_mvm_sta_tx_agg_start(struct iwl_mvm *mvm, struct ieee80211_vif *vif,
 		ret = IEEE80211_AMPDU_TX_START_IMMEDIATE;
 	} else {
 		tid_data->state = IWL_EMPTYING_HW_QUEUE_ADDBA;
-		ret = 0;
+		ret = IEEE80211_AMPDU_TX_START_DELAY_ADDBA;
 	}
 
 out:
